    "body": "### Describe the bug\n\n`__init__` and `__cinit__` methods cannot take fused types (and memory views of fused types) as parameters. However when the user writes such an `__init__` method, the Cython compiler doesn't recognize this as an error and happily generates C code that fails to compile.\n\n### Code to reproduce the behaviour:\n\n```cython\ncimport cython\n\ncdef class A:\n    cdef readonly cython.bint was_given_int\n\n    def __cinit__(self, cython.integral val) -> None:\n        if cython.integral is int:\n            self.was_given_int = True\n        else:\n            self.was_given_int = False\n```\n\n\n### Expected behaviour\n\nCython should have either generated valid C code or raised an error during cythonization\n\n### OS\n\nmacOS\n\n### Python version\n\n3.13.3\n\n### Cython version\n\n3.1.2\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
